Theoretical Direction of Maximum Horizontal Stress in PoR reference system

Source: R/model_shmax.R
PoR_shmax.Rd

Models the direction of maximum horizontal stress \(\sigma_{\text{Hmax}}\) in the Euler pole (Pole of Rotation) cooridnate reference system. When type of plate boundary is given, it also gives the deviation from the theoretically predicted azimuth of \(\sigma_{\text{Hmax}}\), the deviation, and the normalized \(\chi^2\) statistics.

Usage

PoR_shmax(df, euler, type = c("in", "out", "right", "left"))

Arguments

df

data.frame containing the coordinates of the point(s) (lat, lon), the orientation of \(\sigma_{\text{Hmax}}\) azi and its standard deviation unc (optional)

euler

data.frame containing the coordinates of the Euler pole for the plate boundary (lat, lon)

type

Character. Type of plate boundary (optional). Can be "out", "in", "right", or "left" for outward, inward, right-lateral, or left-lateral moving plate boundaries, respectively.

Value

Either a numeric vector of the azimuths in the transformed coordinate system, or a "data.frame" with

"azi.PoR"

the transformed azimuths,

"prd"

the predicted azimuths,

"dev"

the deviation, and

"nchisq"

the normalized \(\chi^2\) statistics.

Details

According to the theory, the azimuth of \(\sigma_{\text{Hmax}}\) in the pole of rotation reference system is approximate 0 (or 180), 45, 90, 135 degrees if the stress is sourced by an outward, sinistral, inward, or dextral moving plate boundary, respectively. directions of \(\sigma_{\text{Hmax}}\) with respect to the four plate boundary types.

See also

model_shmax() to compute the theoretical orientation of \(\sigma_\text{Hmax}\) in the geographical reference system. misfit_shmax() to compute the deviation of the modeled direction from the observed direction of \(\sigma_\text{Hmax}\). norm_chisq() to calculate the normalized \(\chi^2\) statistics.
